      <h1>Privacy Policy for Taurion Pte Ltd</h1>
<div class="text">
Last updated 2024-03-31

Welcome to taurion.ai ("the Service"), provided by Taurion Pte Ltd ("the Company"). In addition to our Privacy Policy, by using our payment processing services through Stripe, you are subject to Stripe's Privacy Policy and Terms of Service. Please review these policies to understand how your data is handled by Stripe. We deeply respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. Before using our website, we kindly ask you to review our updated Privacy Policy, along with our Terms & Conditions. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect information from our valued visitors ("the Users") on taurion.ai and any future products by the Company.

Data Protection and Security

We prioritize the security of your personal data and are dedicated to maintaining your privacy. The Company has implemented technical and organizational measures to safeguard personal data against unauthorized access, disclosure, loss, or destruction. The processing of User data by the Company serves the following purposes:
Fulfilling legal obligations associated with taurion.ai.  Providing marketing and advertising services, including sending commercial information.  Using ICT end devices and automated trigger systems for marketing purposes.  Profiling Users based on behavior, interests, credibility, and preferences.  Sharing personal data with essential entities to fulfill our obligations while disclosing only the minimum necessary information. Data Collection and Analysis
The Company may collect information on User activity and behavior to analyze market trends, assess website traffic, and generate statistics. This data helps us gauge interest in our content, enhance website functionality, and fulfill responsibilities related to anti-money laundering and counterterrorism financing. We assure that personal data processing adheres to relevant laws and respects users' rights.

Sources of Data Collection
Users provide most of the data directly to our Company, collected when you:  Register online or execute a function in any of our products or services.  Voluntarily complete a survey or provide feedback on our websites.  Use or view our website via your browser's cookies or indirectly from other websites that use our embedded cookies. How we use your data  Our company collects your data for the following purposes:  Processing your orders and managing your account.  Emailing you with special offers on other products and services relevant to you.
Enhancing our services and products. With your consent, we may share your data with partner companies to extend their services and products to you. Upon processing your request, we may transmit your data to relevant parties for meaningful analysis.
Processing payments through our integrated payment processor, Stripe, including the collection of necessary billing information to facilitate transactions securely.

How we store your data

Our Company securely stores your data using encryption on AWS. Your personal data will be retained until you request its deletion.
Marketing  Our Company aims to share information about our products and services, along with those offered by our partner companies. If
you've agreed to receive marketing communications, you can opt out at any time by emailing business@taurion.ai. User Rights and Data Control
As a User, you have specific rights regarding your personal information. These include access, correction, updating, removal, processing limitation, data portability, objection, withdrawal of consent, and the right to file a complaint. To exercise these rights, contact us at business@taurion.ai

Rights Summary

The right to access: Request copies of your personal data.
The right to rectification: Ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data.
The right to erasure: Request the deletion of your personal data under specific conditions.
The right to restrict processing: Request a restriction on processing your data under certain circumstances.
The right to data portability: Request the transfer of your data collected by our Company.
We respond to requests within a month.

Legal Basis for Processing Personal Information

The legal basis for processing personal information includes the performance of a contract, user consent, legitimate interests pursued by the Company, and compliance with applicable laws.

Retention of Personal Information

We retain personal information as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy and to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce policies.

Third-Party Services and Cookies

To enhance User experience, taurion uses cookies for various purposes, including functionality and advertising. Users can manage cookie settings through their web browser. "Do Not Track" signals are not processed presently.

More Information on Cookies
For more information about cookies, visit allaboutcookies.org. Privacy Policies of Other Websites
Our privacy policy applies only to our website. When you follow links to external websites, review their privacy policies. Changes to Our Privacy Policy  Our Company periodically reviews and updates its privacy policy, posting changes on this webpage with the update date. Log Files and Third-Party Advertisers
taurion.ai uses log files for standard procedures, and third-party ad servers may collect information for tailored advertising. Children's Information
taurion.ai does not knowingly collect Personal Identifiable Information from children under 13. If you suspect your child provided such information, contact us for prompt removal.

Third-Party Privacy Policies

This Privacy Policy is not applicable to other advertisers or websites linked from taurion.ai. Review their Privacy Policies for insights and opt-out instructions.

Online Privacy Policy Only

This Privacy Policy is for online activities on taurion.ai and does not extend to offline activities or information gathered through channels aside from this website.

Global Data Processing
For global operations, personal information may be transferred, stored, and processed worldwide with suitable safeguards. Billing Information
Any payment processor employed by the Company, including Stripe, is strictly prohibited from retaining or utilizing billing information for purposes beyond payment processing. Please review Stripe's Privacy Policy for more information on how they handle your billing information.
These changes aim to enhance clarity, transparency, and user understanding while emphasizing the Company's commitment to privacy and data security.

Consent and Contact Information
By utilizing our website, you express consent to our Privacy Policy and agree to its terms. If you have queries, concerns, or
complaints concerning this Privacy Policy, please reach out to us at business@taurion.ai. How to contact the appropriate authority
Should you wish to report a complain or if you feel that Our Company has not addressed your concern in a satisfactory manner, you may contact the Information Commissioner's Office.
As an individual or data subject, you can file a complaint to your Data Protection Authority if you feel your GDPR-guaranteed rights were violated.
